A.5 Implementation Details 

Object frame-level embeddings of the visual data are generated with two models, Obj(IN) and 
Obj(IG). Obj(IN) is an SENet-154 model [24] (pretrained on ImageNet for the task of image classi-
fication) from frames extracted at 25 fps, where each frame is resized to 224 ? 224 pixels. Obj(IG) 
is a ResNext-101 [60] pretrained on Instagram hashtags [37], using the same frame preparation
